Parliament, Tuesday, 18 August 2020 – The Standing Committee on Finance will tomorrow morning hold a three-hour virtual meeting, from 09:00 to 12:00 to deliberate and vote on the Disaster Management Tax Relief Bill and Disaster Management Tax Administration Bill. The two Bills were first tabled to Parliament by the National Treasury and the South African Revenue Services (SARS) on 24 June 2020, presented to a joint meeting of the Standing Committee on Finance, as well as the Select Committee on Finance on 14 July 2020. The committees then held public hearings on 22 July 2020. All submissions made during the public hearing can be found below: absa bank covid19 bill comments the standing committee on finance and select committee
